    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs pass the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 and percent-difference < 10% acceptance criteria. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 single-configuration scenario and no extrapolation is claimed. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
